        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 7:52PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 752 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Warrenton, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke Rapids, Louisburg, Warrenton, Norlina, Littleton, Weldon,
Castalia, Macon, Centerville, and Glenview.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
